  "text": "Besides the algebraic properties, it is also important to investigate the geometric aspects of the BCJ numerators. The geometry of the scalar amplitudes, namely the cubic structures, is scrutinized in the language of associahedron in [69, 72, 73] . There can be ways to dress these geometries with numerators encoding the kinematic information, such that the dressed geometries capture the properties of other theories, such as gauge theory and gravity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
